Jose Mourinho faces another of his former clubs this weekend, when Tottenham Hotspur welcome Chelsea in the Premier League. The Blues have seen their fine form falter recently and a loss to Mourinho’s men, will see Spurs overtake them into fourth place. The Portuguese has only lost once since he took over – a 2-1 defeat to another ex-team, Manchester United. Kick off is 5.30pm West African time. Tottenham XI vs Chelsea: Gazzaniga, Aurier, Alderweireld, Sanchez, Vertonghen, Dier, Sissoko, Dele, Son, Lucas, Kane Chelsea XI vs Tottenham: Kepa, Rudiger, Tomori, Zouma, Azpilicueta, Kante, Kovacic, Alonso, Willian, Mount, Abraham Sunday, December 22
